==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Descension
<hw>De*scen"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>descension</ets>, L. <ets>descensio</ets>. See
<er>Descent</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of going downward; descent;
falling or sinking; declension; degradation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oblique descension</b></col> <fld>(Astron.)</fld>,
<cd>the degree or arc of the equator which descends, with a celestial
object, below the horizon of an oblique sphere.</cd> -- <col><b>Right
descension</b></col>, <cd>the degree or arc of the equator which
descends below the horizon of a right sphere at the same time with the
object.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 397 --></p>

<p><ent>Descensional</ent>⟦br⟧
